title: ValueError: too many values to unpack (expected 2)
body:
**Your Operating system and DeepLabCut version** Windows 10 Pro 64bit, with an Anaconda Env, & DeepLabCut 2.1.9 **Describe the problem** After labeling all body points of interest, we use the GUI to 'check labels' and 'create skeleton'. When we click check labels, we receive an error (shown below). Thanks for the help!
Code output

[Creating images with labels by ANT. Traceback (most recent call last): File "C:\Users\Ant-Lab\.conda\envs\DLC-GPU\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\gui\label_frames.py", line 132, in check_labelF deeplabcut.check_labels(self.config, visualizeindividuals=False) File "C:\Users\Ant-Lab\.conda\envs\DLC-GPU\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\generate_training_dataset\trainingsetmanipulation.py", line 506, in check_labels color_by=color_by, File "C:\Users\Ant-Lab\.conda\envs\DLC-GPU\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\utils\visualization.py", line 262, in make_labeled_images_from_dataframe for bp1, bp2 in cfg["skeleton"]: ValueError: too many values to unpack (expected 2)]

**Additional context** I'm thinking it has something to do with the config file. Other issues reported seem to suggest it is because of extra dots (or periods) in the path. However we do not have that. See config file attached. [ [config_copy.txt](https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/files/5811123/config_copy.txt) ](url)
